<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                        <head>No. 122.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Flores</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-05-13"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 13,
                                1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I arrived to-day and will call upon you to-morrow. I respectfully request
                            that you should telegraph to American agents in Ecuador to: stop any
                            proceedings in the Santos affair till you have heard me.</p>
                        <closer><signed>ANTONIO FLORES,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Ecuador
                                Minister.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>